Key Match Events: Romain Saiss scored the opening goal after Hakim Ziyech played a hot free-kick
Novatus Miroshi received a red card with 20 minutes left to play
Youssef En-Nesyri sealed the victory with a goal
Pre-Game Insights: Tanzania is ranked 121 in the FIFA rankings, while Morocco is ranked 13
Morocco is the highest-ranked African team participating in the tournament
Morocco aims to carry the form that saw them reach the World Cup semi-finals in 2022
Tanzania has never won a match in previous Afcon appearances and has conceded goals in every match
Tanzania has scored the fewest goals among all 24 teams in qualifiers
Post-Match Reflections: Coach Walid Regragui expressed caution about the hype surrounding Morocco's status as favorites
The game was expected to be challenging for Tanzania due to Morocco's star-studded team
Miscellaneous Highlights: Tanzania's Novatus Miroshi received a second yellow card leading to a red card
Azzedine Ounahi had to leave the field for medical treatment
